cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with few-shot learning for video action recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and metric-based algorithms, which are common in machine learning and deep learning research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper deals with video data, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia), and involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of different video encoder architectures, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
